    public class SlimmClassifier
extends ClassifierModuleImpl
implements ClassifierModule
    This BioModule builds the scripts used to call SLIMM for classification of WGS data.

      • buildScript

        public List<List<String>> buildScript(List<File> files)
                               throws Exception
        Build 2 bash script lines per sample to classify unpaired WGS reads.

        Example lines:

        • bowtie2 --no-unal --k 60 -p 8 -q --mm -x /database/slimm/5K/AB_5K -U ./input/sample42.fq.gz 2> ./temp/sample42_alignmentReport.txt | samtools view -bS -> ./temp/sample42.bam
        • slimm -m /database/slimm/5K/slimmDB_5K -o ./output/ ./temp/sample42.bam
        Specified by:

      • buildScriptForPairedReads

        public List<List<String>> buildScriptForPairedReads(List<File> files)
                                             throws Exception
        Build 2 bash script lines per sample to classify paired WGS reads.

        Example lines:

        • bowtie2 --no-unal --k 60 -p 8 -q --mm -x /database/slimm/5K/AB_5K -1 ./input/sample42_R1.fq.gz -2 ./input/sample42_R2.fq.gz 2> ./temp/sample42_alignmentReport.txt | samtools view -bS -> ./temp/sample42.bam
        • slimm -m /database/slimm/5K/slimmDB_5K -o ./output/ ./temp/sample42.bam

      • getClassifierParams

        public String getClassifierParams()
                           throws Exception
        Description copied from class: ClassifierModuleImpl
        Get optional classifier switches by appending "--" to each value in the list parameter if defined in the Config file. Classifiers that use a single "-" must be override this method. To simplify the Config, default values for exe.classifier can be defined by replacing "exe" with a classifier type (rdp, qiime, kraken, metaphlan, or slimm). For example, if exe.classifer is missing or blank and getClassifierType() returns "rdp" the property rdp.classifier will be used in place of exe.classifier. This allows all classifiers to be defined in a file such as standard.properties.
        Specified by:
        getClassifierParams in interface ClassifierModule
        Overrides:
        getClassifierParams in class ClassifierModuleImpl
        Returns:
        String containing formatted switches to append to the executable
        Throws:
        Exception - if defined but invalid
